text: Teka Place Car Park is conveniently located for easy access to nearby shops and Little India. However, the space is a bit tight, so larger vehicles may find it challenging to navigate. Overall, a practical option if youâ€™re visiting the area, but it can get crowded during peak times.

The car park is spacious and I could get a parking lot easily. I always park there whenever I visit Serangoon road. It is very near to Little India Archade and there are many restaurants around that area.
Spiral 2 way to carpark. Level 3 is the lowest parking level. Generally has lot for parking in the morning at around 7.45am.
Expensive charges for motorcycle and embarkation not very clear for motorcycle parking. 5th floor connect to link bridge to tekka place mall.
Less congested car park but bit expensive
